text: IFK Öxnehaga is a sports club in Öxnehaga in Huskvarna in Sweden. It was established on 10 April 1955 as IFK Huskvarna. The women's soccer team in the Swedish second division during the late 1990s and the early 2000s. When IFK Jönköping was disbanded following the 1998 season the activity of that club was transferred to IFK öxnehaga. The club won both the Småland women's and girls' district championship in 1999. ==References== ==Other websites== * Official website Category:1955 establishments in Sweden Category:Huskvarna Category:Swedish football clubs
